WEBVTT

00:29.217 --> 00:30.302
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

00:33.388 --> 00:35.014
CHARACTERS, EVENTS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND PLACES IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

00:35.015 --> 00:36.308
ALL CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
FILMED IN A SAFE ENVIRONMENT

00:36.892 --> 00:37.975
Mr. Park.

00:37.976 --> 00:40.771
Mr. Park, did you see…

00:49.279 --> 00:50.571
I can't reach him.

00:50.572 --> 00:52.741
He took his car and left

00:53.909 --> 00:55.369
after 2:00 a.m. last night.

00:56.411 --> 00:57.828
He has a bad fever.

00:57.829 --> 00:59.955
He's not in a state to drive right now.

00:59.956 --> 01:01.874
Then I should call the police--

01:01.875 --> 01:02.876
Seonu Chan!

01:04.669 --> 01:07.129
- Ben.
- Is he here?

01:07.130 --> 01:09.132
I haven't been able to reach him.

01:09.841 --> 01:11.717
Why? Is something wrong?

01:11.718 --> 01:14.429
He sent an email to the headquarters

01:15.055 --> 01:16.639
saying he'll quit.

01:16.640 --> 01:17.723
What?

01:17.724 --> 01:19.141
I can't get in touch with him,

01:19.142 --> 01:21.895
and they said he even deleted
his email account already.

01:23.146 --> 01:24.648
He must have vanished on purpose.

01:25.232 --> 01:26.566
Goodness.

01:35.033 --> 01:36.868
He's been planning it
for a long time.

01:37.452 --> 01:40.329
He said he wanted to be with you

01:40.330 --> 01:42.040
through spring, summer, fall, and winter.

01:42.499 --> 01:44.876
He said he'd explain everything soon.

01:47.212 --> 01:49.923
But it looks like
it's broken beyond repair.

01:50.966 --> 01:52.134
He was hesitant

01:53.760 --> 01:56.012
because his memories weren't fully intact.

01:56.847 --> 01:59.140
And he was worried that

01:59.141 --> 02:02.144
acting rashly would only hurt you.

02:02.894 --> 02:04.813
He was going through a hard time too,

02:06.523 --> 02:09.443
but his mind was only focused on you.

02:11.236 --> 02:14.573
But it seems like
he missed several chances to tell you.

02:15.532 --> 02:17.700
There was that issue
with your grandma too.

02:19.661 --> 02:20.662
I…

02:23.415 --> 02:25.000
made him leave.

02:25.542 --> 02:27.543
You don't have to look at me
or listen to me.

02:27.544 --> 02:28.754
Please, just look at this.

02:30.005 --> 02:31.172
So please…

02:31.173 --> 02:33.467
No exceptions.
Don't let anyone in my office.

02:35.051 --> 02:37.219
Don't ever show up in front of me again.

02:37.220 --> 02:39.805
You just pushed me back into winter again.

02:39.806 --> 02:42.184
I should have listened to him at least.

02:42.976 --> 02:44.269
What do I do?

02:45.729 --> 02:48.356
Regardless of whose roommate
he was seven years ago,

02:50.317 --> 02:52.277
what secrets he hid…

02:55.322 --> 02:57.699
or what he did wrong,

02:59.785 --> 03:01.620
I really can't hate him.

03:35.237 --> 03:37.489
I'm only visiting.
I came from Boston.
:cue

03:50.335 --> 03:52.002
END OF TRIAL

03:55.048 --> 03:56.298
A three-month trial!

03:56.299 --> 03:59.593
As soon as the three months is over,
I'll disappear without a trace.

03:59.594 --> 04:01.721
I'm not someone who will leave
in three months,

04:02.847 --> 04:04.974
nor someone who might never come back.

04:04.975 --> 04:06.268
Ms. Song.

04:06.851 --> 04:09.603
No, Haran. I want to stay with you.

04:09.604 --> 04:13.275
I'm going to use that trial
for the rest of my life.

04:14.859 --> 04:16.987
When did he come here?

04:22.742 --> 04:24.244
Where did you go, Seonu Chan?

04:30.292 --> 04:32.459
Then that accident…

04:32.460 --> 04:34.962
Yes. It was all because of you.

04:34.963 --> 04:37.841
You caused the accident,
and it killed Hyeokchan.

04:49.227 --> 04:50.228
He…

04:51.104 --> 04:52.147
disappeared.

04:53.982 --> 04:57.777
The Seonu Chan I know
would never just leave like that.

04:59.070 --> 05:01.239
I'm sure there must be a reason.

05:02.699 --> 05:04.659
But I didn't even give him
a chance to talk.

05:05.660 --> 05:06.870
So I'm regretting it.

05:10.457 --> 05:13.084
You, he, and Hyeokchan knew each other

05:13.793 --> 05:14.878
in Boston, right?

05:17.547 --> 05:18.673
Yes.

05:20.467 --> 05:21.967
His disappearance

05:21.968 --> 05:24.429
seems to be connected
to what happened seven years ago.

05:25.597 --> 05:27.390
What happened back then?

05:28.433 --> 05:29.434
Please tell me.

05:30.060 --> 05:31.353
I have to know.

05:34.314 --> 05:35.398
I'm sorry.

05:36.942 --> 05:38.151
Seven years ago,

05:39.235 --> 05:41.154
I did something bad to you.

05:43.490 --> 05:46.117
I met Hyeokchan for the first time
at a hospital.

05:47.494 --> 05:51.288
He and I were both waiting for a surgery.

05:51.289 --> 05:53.249
He was pretty stressed back then

05:54.000 --> 05:56.294
because he couldn't reach you often.

05:58.296 --> 05:59.297
What time is it?

06:00.006 --> 06:03.467
I missed his calls again.

06:05.470 --> 06:07.763
Did you download it?
Can you see my message?

06:07.764 --> 06:09.140
Yes, I can see it!

06:09.891 --> 06:11.266
You kept missing my calls,

06:11.267 --> 06:15.021
so I thought we could at least
send each other messages on our laptops.

06:18.024 --> 06:20.442
I'm going to bed now. Love you.

06:20.443 --> 06:22.361
Oh, no…

06:22.362 --> 06:24.488
The silk georgette…

06:24.489 --> 06:27.074
- Haran, the draping fabric.
-  Coming.

06:27.075 --> 06:28.534
Sorry, I'm in a bit of a hurry.

06:28.535 --> 06:30.203
I'll call you back later. Sorry.

06:34.624 --> 06:36.251
You shouldn't be smoking.

06:37.919 --> 06:38.920
None of your business.

06:39.838 --> 06:40.839
Are you Korean?

06:46.136 --> 06:48.345
Let's meet up and chat from time to time.

06:48.346 --> 06:49.931
We're both lonely students here.

06:53.017 --> 06:54.476
We were the same age,

06:54.477 --> 06:57.020
and we were both lonely students
studying abroad.

06:57.021 --> 06:58.981
So we grew close quickly.

07:02.444 --> 07:04.486
You were the only one
who could bring this.

07:04.487 --> 07:07.364
But I didn't have your number,
so I asked the T.A.

07:07.365 --> 07:09.159
Sorry for the hassle.

07:14.622 --> 07:15.706
My number.

07:15.707 --> 07:17.959
Call me if you need anything.
Not too often, though.
:cue

07:22.547 --> 07:24.590
Sorry.

07:24.591 --> 07:26.717
I heard
he wasn't close with his roommate,

07:26.718 --> 07:28.969
but he asked Seonu Chan for a favor,

07:28.970 --> 07:30.637
and that's when I first met him.

07:30.638 --> 07:33.599
- Who's that? Your friend?
- No, just my roommate.

07:36.770 --> 07:40.522
We developed feelings
for each other as we grew close.

07:42.776 --> 07:45.110
We kept seeing each other
after we were discharged.

07:45.111 --> 07:47.571
That's when Hyeokchan
started making excuses

07:47.572 --> 07:49.699
and asking his roommate for favors.

07:50.408 --> 07:52.451
He canceled his plans to go to Korea

07:52.452 --> 07:54.495
and went traveling with me
during vacation,

07:54.496 --> 07:57.331
but he accidentally took
his roommate's laptop instead.

07:57.332 --> 07:58.917
And during that one month,

08:00.668 --> 08:03.296
I think Seonu Chan was chatting

08:04.631 --> 08:05.882
with you

08:06.508 --> 08:07.634
on Hyeokchan's laptop.

08:08.551 --> 08:12.679
Hyeokchan had already made up his mind
to break up with you.

08:12.680 --> 08:14.474
I'm sorry, but the reason was me.

08:16.684 --> 08:19.270
Seonu Chan didn't start it intentionally.

08:19.979 --> 08:23.649
It was Hyeokchan's mistake,
and he asked him to message you.

08:24.734 --> 08:26.986
Did you have fun
chatting with me like that?

08:27.862 --> 08:30.573
Did you build some kind of fantasy
and start liking me?

08:32.116 --> 08:33.701
Even though I knew about you,

08:35.578 --> 08:36.955
I wanted Hyeokchan.

08:38.373 --> 08:39.374
I'm sorry.

08:44.587 --> 08:46.089
All right.

08:50.927 --> 08:52.303
Seonu Chan…

08:53.638 --> 08:55.098
disappeared because of me.

09:00.228 --> 09:02.646
If his bleeding
was caused by the shrapnel,

09:02.647 --> 09:04.273
it may be accompanied

09:04.274 --> 09:06.775
by neurological symptoms
such as auditory or visual hallucinations.

09:06.776 --> 09:09.486
There have even been reports
of memory distortion

09:09.487 --> 09:11.363
in severe cases like this.

09:11.364 --> 09:13.241
Memory distortion?

09:13.950 --> 09:16.118
His memories are distorted?

09:16.119 --> 09:17.411
I had no idea

09:17.412 --> 09:20.747
he'd been suffering so much
from the explosion back then.

09:20.748 --> 09:25.503
He told me never to tell you
about Hyeokchan and me,

09:26.045 --> 09:27.880
but I thought I should tell you.

09:27.881 --> 09:29.465
I get that about Hyeokchan,

09:30.091 --> 09:31.259
but what do you mean?

09:31.926 --> 09:33.010
Why did he disappear--

09:33.011 --> 09:34.888
I did something…

09:36.097 --> 09:38.808
I shouldn't have done,
as a person and as a doctor.

09:51.738 --> 09:52.988
Your passport? Why?

09:52.989 --> 09:54.740
I'm going to Boston to meet Chan,

09:54.741 --> 09:56.283
since we have four days off.

09:56.284 --> 09:57.911
What? Really?

09:58.745 --> 10:00.662
You seem different these days.

10:00.663 --> 10:01.997
What? Why?

10:01.998 --> 10:05.834
Just a while back,
you didn't seem that into him.

10:05.835 --> 10:07.294
Was that a month ago?

10:07.295 --> 10:09.505
What's this sudden burst of affection?

10:10.381 --> 10:11.466
I don't know, either.

10:11.925 --> 10:14.968
When we were together,
I didn't notice him much,

10:14.969 --> 10:17.930
but I feel like I can see him clearer
when I'm chatting with him

10:17.931 --> 10:19.307
without seeing or hearing him.

10:19.849 --> 10:23.645
I can tell how much he understands me
and how well we click.

10:24.479 --> 10:27.773
Maybe it's because of this pen.

10:30.902 --> 10:32.028
What do I do?

10:36.324 --> 10:37.367
What do I do?

10:39.619 --> 10:42.747
What do I do?

10:53.549 --> 10:55.550
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON
:cue

10:57.470 --> 10:58.805
Mr. Yeon.

11:00.056 --> 11:01.515
I'm going to the factory.

11:01.516 --> 11:05.477
I'm meeting Mr. Chae
in front of the factory at 4:00 p.m.

11:05.478 --> 11:09.148
I heard it's in Gangwon-do Province.
It's pretty far, so drive safely.

11:11.192 --> 11:14.236
But what happened to your keychain?

11:14.237 --> 11:16.530
Oh, I'm taking the company car
since it's far away.

11:16.531 --> 11:19.491
Ah. Sorry, I can't come with you.

11:19.492 --> 11:21.868
No need to apologize for that.

11:21.869 --> 11:24.830
I know you're insanely busy
with Ms. Kim absent.

11:24.831 --> 11:27.000
I'll see you later, then.

11:31.587 --> 11:33.298
It's going to take so long.

11:36.175 --> 11:38.135
I have to cheer him up.

11:39.929 --> 11:40.930
Smile.

11:45.810 --> 11:46.811
Huh?

11:50.315 --> 11:51.316
"Kim."

11:55.611 --> 11:56.779
YOUGYUM

12:01.743 --> 12:03.786
Why isn't he picking up?

12:10.501 --> 12:13.045
Yang Changmo.
Do you know where Yougyum is?

12:13.046 --> 12:15.130
He's taking his stuff
out of his locker.

12:15.131 --> 12:16.549
He says he's quitting baseball.

12:17.342 --> 12:18.842
- What?
- He said

12:18.843 --> 12:21.220
he won't be able to become
a pro athlete anyway.

12:30.188 --> 12:31.230
CHA YOUGYUM

12:45.703 --> 12:47.287
In 2007,

12:47.288 --> 12:49.623
Park Jisung got knee surgery

12:49.624 --> 12:52.292
and returned to Manchester United
after nine months.

12:52.293 --> 12:54.379
He made it
to the Champions League semifinals.

12:59.342 --> 13:01.134
In 2025,

13:01.135 --> 13:04.721
Shohei Ohtani returned
from two elbow surgeries

13:04.722 --> 13:06.390
and threw even faster than before,

13:06.391 --> 13:09.142
rewriting his Major League career records.

13:09.143 --> 13:10.686
And in 2015,

13:11.270 --> 13:12.688
Ryu Hyunjin…

13:14.565 --> 13:15.900
had a shoulder tear…

13:16.651 --> 13:17.652
Shoulder tear…

13:20.279 --> 13:21.280
Hadam, stop.

13:22.657 --> 13:23.658
That's enough.

13:24.826 --> 13:25.827
I'm sorry.

13:27.578 --> 13:28.913
I'm really sorry,

13:29.831 --> 13:30.915
but I can't make it.

13:32.250 --> 13:33.501
Those athletes

13:34.377 --> 13:36.796
took much longer to recover than expected.

13:37.922 --> 13:39.298
But they returned stronger.

13:40.299 --> 13:42.592
You don't have to play baseball.

13:42.593 --> 13:45.053
And you don't have to join
the Major League.

13:45.054 --> 13:46.139
But…

13:46.848 --> 13:49.182
if you give up now
without trying until the end,

13:49.183 --> 13:50.560
all you can do later…

13:52.395 --> 13:53.479
is regret it.

13:55.189 --> 13:57.108
Let's try everything we can until the end.

13:57.608 --> 13:59.068
You can give up then.

14:00.027 --> 14:02.029
Until you find something else
you want to do,

14:03.197 --> 14:04.823
I'll take care of you, so--

14:04.824 --> 14:05.825
I'm scared.

14:08.828 --> 14:11.998
I'm scared I'll turn out to be nothing
even after I try.

14:16.085 --> 14:17.086
Then,

14:17.920 --> 14:19.964
you can be the Cha Yougyum

14:21.007 --> 14:23.134
who at least tried his best until the end.

14:23.759 --> 14:24.760
You can be that.

14:25.553 --> 14:28.054
Then you won't turn out to be nothing.

14:28.055 --> 14:29.599
You helped me stay strong

14:30.725 --> 14:32.310
when I was having a rough time.

14:33.811 --> 14:35.813
So it's my turn to help you stand back up.

14:36.272 --> 14:39.399
Even if you give up baseball,
I won't let go of your hand.

14:39.400 --> 14:41.068
I'll stay with you until the end.

14:44.280 --> 14:45.406
So let's not…

14:46.949 --> 14:48.075
run away from this.

14:55.333 --> 14:56.334
I'll give it a try.

14:57.752 --> 15:00.588
We can cry later if I still can't do it.

15:01.047 --> 15:02.381
But right now,

15:04.217 --> 15:05.218
let's try this.

15:13.893 --> 15:14.894
REPORTER CHAE HYUNWOO

15:15.436 --> 15:17.062
- Yes, Mr. Chae.
-  Hey.

15:17.063 --> 15:19.648
We rescheduled the factory visit
to next Wednesday.

15:19.649 --> 15:20.774
Can you join us then?

15:20.775 --> 15:22.026
What are you talking about?

15:22.652 --> 15:24.861
Ms. Song just left for Yeongwol.
:cue

15:24.862 --> 15:27.948
Huh? I left her a message
saying it got canceled.

15:27.949 --> 15:30.618
We can't enter
because of a blizzard warning.

15:32.578 --> 15:34.413
MR. YEON

15:37.291 --> 15:42.087
Hello, this is Song Hayeong's phone
that she leaves lying around every day.

15:48.594 --> 15:49.928
Chae Hyunwoo.

15:49.929 --> 15:52.889
You should've checked
to see if she got the message.

15:55.851 --> 15:57.227
Send me the address.

16:01.607 --> 16:02.691
I'm sorry.

16:02.692 --> 16:05.778
Something urgent came up,
so I have to postpone the meeting.

16:07.029 --> 16:08.531
I'm really sorry.

16:17.415 --> 16:20.459
I can't believe this.

16:21.002 --> 16:22.003
What is this?

16:23.170 --> 16:24.171
Huh?

16:26.299 --> 16:28.884
This is driving me crazy.

16:33.306 --> 16:36.099
You can't enter
because of the heavy snow.

16:36.100 --> 16:38.644
You have to head back, all right?

16:42.023 --> 16:43.481
Hang on.

16:43.482 --> 16:44.691
Excuse me.

16:44.692 --> 16:46.235
You can't enter. Excuse me!

16:47.028 --> 16:49.362
Sir! Wait!

16:51.532 --> 16:55.244
My car won't start,
and I don't even have my phone.

16:56.620 --> 16:58.956
It's so cold.

17:01.125 --> 17:04.754
You can't fall asleep,
Song Hayeong.

17:05.254 --> 17:07.173
Am I going to die here?

17:08.841 --> 17:09.884
Well…

17:10.634 --> 17:13.137
I've lived a happy life.

17:13.763 --> 17:16.474
I was so stupid.

17:17.558 --> 17:18.976
Ms. Song Hayeong.

17:19.977 --> 17:21.269
Ms. Song!

17:21.270 --> 17:24.397
Why am I hallucinating Mr. Yeon's voice
in a moment like this?

17:29.028 --> 17:30.029
Huh?

17:32.156 --> 17:34.075
Mr. Yeon?

17:37.078 --> 17:38.079
Ms. Song.

17:39.830 --> 17:41.207
Are you all right?

17:41.666 --> 17:43.834
Is that really you, Mr. Yeon?

17:44.835 --> 17:45.878
Yes, it's me.

17:48.964 --> 17:50.091
Everything's okay now.

17:53.177 --> 17:56.097
I'll call a car service right away.
Just a moment.

17:59.558 --> 18:00.559
Wow.

18:11.862 --> 18:14.114
I'm fine, so take this…

18:14.115 --> 18:15.157
No.

18:15.825 --> 18:18.243
Keep it on.

18:18.244 --> 18:21.163
Don't make me get the wrong idea again.

18:21.622 --> 18:25.667
You would've rushed over
even if it were Haran or Hadam, right?

18:31.257 --> 18:32.633
I'm not sure.

18:34.009 --> 18:35.010
What?

18:37.263 --> 18:38.723
I think I was wrong.

18:39.515 --> 18:40.640
What…

18:40.641 --> 18:41.809
I think I do see you…

18:43.769 --> 18:45.229
as more than a colleague.

18:55.030 --> 18:57.366
I told myself I couldn't dare to,

18:58.701 --> 19:00.286
since you're Ms. Kim's granddaughter.

19:02.496 --> 19:06.250
So I guess I turned away from my feelings.

19:10.963 --> 19:12.965
How could I not be attracted

19:14.633 --> 19:17.928
to someone like you?

19:21.474 --> 19:22.892
I know it's pretty late,

19:23.809 --> 19:27.313
but if you're really okay
with someone like me…

19:32.443 --> 19:33.861
would it be all right

19:35.321 --> 19:36.530
for me to like you?
:cue

19:54.131 --> 19:55.174
Gosh…

19:55.716 --> 19:57.802
Let's clean up this place

19:58.844 --> 20:01.096
so Chan can return anytime.

20:29.583 --> 20:30.668
Yes?

20:32.211 --> 20:34.171
Ms. Song, there's a delivery for you.

20:47.142 --> 20:48.435
Have you been well?

20:49.019 --> 20:50.563
It took a while,

20:51.188 --> 20:53.065
but I put it together.

20:57.945 --> 21:03.033
Restoration begins the moment
you decide to put it back together.

21:03.534 --> 21:04.826
It may take a while,

21:04.827 --> 21:08.998
but as long as you don't give up,
the pieces will come together in the end,

21:09.498 --> 21:11.041
and those pieces

21:11.625 --> 21:14.128
will contain a deeper story
compared to before.

21:14.670 --> 21:16.589
I learned through this job

21:17.631 --> 21:21.552
that miracles begin by not giving up.

21:22.219 --> 21:24.889
If there is anything you wish to fix,

21:25.598 --> 21:30.269
I hope a miracle occurs for you as well.

21:31.645 --> 21:33.606
Not giving up…

21:56.045 --> 21:58.796
The service center refused
since the model is discontinued.

21:58.797 --> 22:00.340
Will you be able to fix it?

22:00.341 --> 22:03.259
I could try if I had new parts for this,

22:03.260 --> 22:07.473
but it'll be hard since this model
was sold briefly over 10 years ago.

22:07.973 --> 22:08.974
I'm sorry.

22:11.477 --> 22:14.437
Would anyone
be able to fix this drawing pad?

22:14.438 --> 22:16.941
I'll repay anyone
who can at least recover the data.

22:20.152 --> 22:22.278
What's this? An old tablet?

22:22.279 --> 22:23.906
A drawing pad like this exists?

22:30.829 --> 22:33.122
Wow,
I used this in middle school.

22:33.123 --> 22:34.917
It's probably stashed somewhere.

22:36.752 --> 22:38.753
I could try
if I had new parts for this.

22:41.507 --> 22:44.717
Are you willing
to sell it to me if you find it?

22:44.718 --> 22:47.137
If you are, please message me.

22:51.725 --> 22:54.144
ARE YOU WILLING
TO SELL IT TO ME IF YOU FIND IT?

23:02.444 --> 23:03.528
Hello?

23:03.529 --> 23:06.030
Are you the one
who left a message saying

23:06.031 --> 23:08.450
- you wanted to buy my drawing pad?
- Yes, I am.

23:09.994 --> 23:12.245
I found a working drawing pad.

23:12.246 --> 23:14.456
The parts are in there,
so you can fix it, right?

23:15.165 --> 23:17.960
I can't guarantee that,
but you can leave it with me.

23:23.590 --> 23:25.091
Thanks to the new parts,

23:25.092 --> 23:28.679
I managed to restore the data
and move it to another device.

23:29.221 --> 23:30.806
to HARAN

23:43.027 --> 23:47.613
1. SUMMER, SEVEN YEARS AGO
IT STARTED WITH WALLS

23:53.704 --> 23:55.121
Hyeokchan and I

23:55.122 --> 23:57.416
were roommates
at the Boston Institute of Technology.

23:57.916 --> 24:00.585
Can you message her back
and say I have to go to the lab?

24:00.586 --> 24:02.129
Do me a solid.

24:05.841 --> 24:09.094
One day, I was about to turn off
Hyeokchan's messenger alarm,

24:09.803 --> 24:11.680
but your words caught my eye.

24:12.556 --> 24:13.891
"Surrounded by walls."

24:14.558 --> 24:16.602
Perhaps because I'd been feeling that way,

24:17.853 --> 24:20.022
I wanted to be someone you could talk to.

24:20.939 --> 24:23.191
I could guess
how lost you would be feeling.

24:23.192 --> 24:24.776
IF IT'S OKAY WITH YOU, YOU CAN TALK TO ME

24:24.777 --> 24:26.820
:cue

24:34.078 --> 24:36.080
All I did was listen to you,

24:36.955 --> 24:39.374
but strangely, it comforted me too.

24:42.878 --> 24:45.464
THANKS FOR LISTENING TO ME COMPLAIN!

24:46.131 --> 24:47.424
I thought

24:48.092 --> 24:50.718
that would be
our first and last conversation.

24:50.719 --> 24:52.012
But…

24:54.181 --> 24:55.807
2. FOUNTAIN PEN, AND ENGRAVING

24:55.808 --> 24:57.976
Around that time,
Hyeokchan hurt his hand badly,

24:58.852 --> 25:00.562
and he asked me for a favor.

25:01.355 --> 25:04.565
Anything that a woman
in her twenties can use.

25:04.566 --> 25:06.400
He wanted to get you a gift,

25:06.401 --> 25:09.238
but he couldn't make time
because of his treatment.

25:09.780 --> 25:11.280
He felt really sorry.

25:11.281 --> 25:14.993
I'm looking for a pen, like…

25:16.036 --> 25:19.498
A pen for efficient design sketches.
Do you have them?

25:20.082 --> 25:22.750
That's when
I remembered what you'd said.

25:22.751 --> 25:27.004
You said you were surrounded by walls
and you couldn't sketch anything.

25:27.005 --> 25:30.591
Hoping it would cheer you up a bit,
I chose a drawing pen.

25:30.592 --> 25:32.177
Okay, I'll take this.

25:32.970 --> 25:36.306
Is it a gift?
I could engrave it if you'd like.

25:41.228 --> 25:42.354
"Haran."

25:42.938 --> 25:44.188
I suddenly remembered

25:44.189 --> 25:47.901
the name Hyeokchan had said
when he was calling you.

25:49.820 --> 25:52.281
The design contest winner is…

25:53.031 --> 25:54.866
Congratulations, Haran.

25:54.867 --> 25:56.285
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE MY SAVIOR.

25:57.536 --> 26:00.831
Hyeokchan was away
to help our professor with some research.

26:02.416 --> 26:05.459
I'm traveling around the East Coast
during vacation.

26:05.460 --> 26:09.256
If our professor asks for me,
say I'm taking a break because of my hand.

26:10.090 --> 26:12.091
Our laptops got switched
by accident back then…

26:13.427 --> 26:16.430
…and soon after,
I had another day where I felt trapped.

26:23.437 --> 26:25.438
How long are you going to keep doing this?

26:25.439 --> 26:28.734
What more do I have to do
to make you stop?

26:30.402 --> 26:32.612
Do you remember

26:32.613 --> 26:36.533
how I said I stood alone
in a harsh winter as well?

26:38.076 --> 26:41.537
I'd been barely holding on,
surrounded by walls,

26:41.538 --> 26:44.457
but just as I was about to give up
and end everything…

26:45.542 --> 26:48.420
…you suddenly spoke to me

26:49.213 --> 26:51.673
right when I was about to die.

26:52.507 --> 26:53.634
"You're…

26:54.760 --> 26:56.177
my savior."

26:56.178 --> 26:58.721
I knew those words weren't meant for me,

26:58.722 --> 27:01.433
but I wanted to cling to them.

27:02.267 --> 27:04.228
You said I was your savior,

27:04.811 --> 27:06.855
but you were the one who saved me.

27:07.940 --> 27:08.941
And that…

27:09.608 --> 27:11.276
gave me reason to keep living.

27:11.902 --> 27:13.237
Song Haran.

27:13.570 --> 27:15.363
You saved me,

27:15.364 --> 27:16.448
seven years ago.

27:17.407 --> 27:18.784
You saved me back then!

27:20.577 --> 27:22.495
Since then…

27:22.496 --> 27:24.748
…I couldn't ignore the messages you sent,

27:25.374 --> 27:26.749
thinking it was Hyeokchan.

27:26.750 --> 27:29.377
GOLDBERG, NEON ALIEN, SMELL OF RAIN
THE PERSON WHO BROADENED MY WORLD

27:30.879 --> 27:33.965
That Gold-something that
helps you sleep. I heard there's no proof.

27:33.966 --> 27:36.175
It's like music to wake you up.

27:38.428 --> 27:40.554
I'd forgotten how to smile,

27:40.555 --> 27:42.724
but I started smiling because of you.

27:44.977 --> 27:46.227
Shocking news.

27:46.228 --> 27:48.646
I was eating lunch,
and there was eggplant in it.

27:48.647 --> 27:49.730
Eggplant?

27:49.731 --> 27:53.317
It's all mushy and squishy,
and it's neon-colored. Yuck!

27:53.318 --> 27:54.569
The taste of a neon alien.

27:56.071 --> 27:57.239
A neon alien…

27:57.656 --> 27:58.906
I grew curious about you...

27:59.992 --> 28:01.243
...and started looking forward

28:02.119 --> 28:04.246
to what interesting stories
you'd tell me next.

28:06.373 --> 28:09.917
My black-and-white life
began to be filled with colors,

28:09.918 --> 28:11.920
and my tiny world

28:12.921 --> 28:14.256
began to grow bigger,

28:14.715 --> 28:17.426
thanks to your messages.

28:18.427 --> 28:21.430
Thank you for helping me
not give up on what I love.

28:21.930 --> 28:23.724
For giving me a reason to keep going.

28:25.559 --> 28:29.688
If there was just a small crack
to breathe through, I could live.

28:30.313 --> 28:34.526
I guess I wanted that pen
to be that "if" for you.

28:36.862 --> 28:39.322
You became that "if" for me,

28:40.323 --> 28:43.201
because I started drawing again,
thanks to you.

28:45.037 --> 28:46.038
Hey, Chan.

28:46.538 --> 28:48.205
Got the dorm maintenance notice.

28:48.206 --> 28:49.416
Thank you.

28:50.500 --> 28:51.876
Wow, you're really good.

28:51.877 --> 28:53.961
You think you can draw me one day?

28:53.962 --> 28:56.422
Uh…  Okay.

28:56.423 --> 28:58.758
- Ah. Good, thanks.
-  And…

28:58.759 --> 29:01.761
for the first time,
I started looking forward to the next day.

29:01.762 --> 29:04.472
The moments I spent talking to you

29:04.473 --> 29:08.143
helped me stay strong
without crumbling down.

29:10.437 --> 29:11.438
:cue

29:11.980 --> 29:13.064
5. THE EXPLOSION

29:13.065 --> 29:14.148
But…

29:14.149 --> 29:18.319
near the end of that summer,
there was an accident.

29:18.320 --> 29:19.488
A lab explosion.

29:21.948 --> 29:25.367
Everyone said I'd die soon
and that I would never wake up.

29:25.368 --> 29:26.452
But…

29:26.453 --> 29:27.496
Chan.

29:27.788 --> 29:28.871
I heard a voice.

29:28.872 --> 29:30.247
I love you.

29:31.416 --> 29:32.875
I love you, Chan.

29:32.876 --> 29:36.213
It was as if that voice
was trying to wake me up.

29:37.881 --> 29:39.883
I woke to that voice,

29:41.426 --> 29:42.719
but I couldn't remember

29:43.345 --> 29:46.014
who called my name and woke me up.

29:48.517 --> 29:51.061
I lost my memories after the accident
for about a year,

29:52.062 --> 29:54.397
but for some reason,

29:55.190 --> 29:56.733
that person's face and voice

29:57.317 --> 30:01.321
kept popping up vividly in my mind.

30:02.114 --> 30:05.617
And when I came to Korea for treatment,
I spotted her by coincidence.

30:06.660 --> 30:07.911
On Christmas Eve,

30:08.620 --> 30:09.913
at Jamsugyo.

30:10.539 --> 30:12.081
I ran after her,

30:12.082 --> 30:15.210
thinking she'd be the one
holding the key to my memories.

30:18.588 --> 30:22.175
But fireworks suddenly went off,
and I remembered the explosion.

30:22.592 --> 30:24.135
All my hazy memories

30:24.136 --> 30:26.471
came flooding back.

30:28.098 --> 30:29.224
That's when I realized

30:30.016 --> 30:33.645
that person
was my old roommate's girlfriend,

30:34.396 --> 30:35.522
and that I was just…

30:36.481 --> 30:41.068
a complete stranger to you.

30:46.992 --> 30:48.325
6. MEMENTO MORI

30:48.326 --> 30:50.661
I immediately left
without a clear destination.

30:50.662 --> 30:52.288
I wanted to get rid of my past.

30:52.289 --> 30:54.331
I'd like a ticket
for the earliest departure anywhere.

30:54.332 --> 30:57.544
But there was one thing
I just couldn't get rid of.

31:00.714 --> 31:03.507
There was someone
who had helped me survive twice.

31:03.508 --> 31:04.592
DRAW

31:04.593 --> 31:06.260
At least for her sake,

31:06.261 --> 31:08.930
I knew I had to stop
living like a dead person.

31:09.514 --> 31:13.059
I got this tattoo
so I wouldn't forget that resolution.

31:13.643 --> 31:14.936
"Memento Mori."

31:17.397 --> 31:22.235
So I struggled for seven years
like I was trying to become someone else,

31:22.777 --> 31:24.278
and at some point,

31:24.279 --> 31:27.281
my environment, surroundings, and I…

31:27.282 --> 31:29.159
had really changed.

31:29.951 --> 31:32.870
It was as if my past did not matter.

31:34.289 --> 31:36.541
7. NICE TO MEET YOU

31:37.792 --> 31:41.378
Then one day, you appeared again

31:41.379 --> 31:44.423
right in front of me, after seven years.

31:44.424 --> 31:45.758
It's nice to meet you.

31:45.759 --> 31:47.968
I'm Song Haran, the lead designer.

31:47.969 --> 31:50.346
I thought I was going to cry.

31:50.347 --> 31:53.933
I was so grateful, and I missed you
and was curious about you, but…

31:53.934 --> 31:55.936
It's nice to meet you. I'm…

31:56.603 --> 31:59.605
You were someone
I shouldn't even think about.

31:59.606 --> 32:01.023
…Seonu Chan.

32:01.024 --> 32:02.566
8. LET'S HAVE FUN LIKE A SPRING PICNIC

32:03.652 --> 32:05.694
If anything happens to you too…

32:05.695 --> 32:06.696
Haran.

32:07.364 --> 32:11.243
At first, I decided to avoid you
so I wouldn't get caught,

32:12.994 --> 32:14.496
but I felt pained

32:15.538 --> 32:16.539
while watching you.

32:18.208 --> 32:21.878
The person who saved me seven years ago
was trapped alone in winter.

32:23.922 --> 32:25.589
I thought I'd regret it later…

32:25.590 --> 32:27.758
It's really valuable to me,
so I have to find it.

32:27.759 --> 32:29.511
So I ended up making a crazy offer.

32:30.470 --> 32:31.762
A three-month trial!

32:31.763 --> 32:33.430
Then let's do this.

32:33.431 --> 32:35.225
It'll be like we're on a spring picnic.

32:35.976 --> 32:36.977
Let's have fun.
:cue

32:46.528 --> 32:48.237
9. GREED

32:48.238 --> 32:51.615
Many things happened between us
after that.

32:59.124 --> 33:01.625
Tell me if it keeps hurting.

33:01.626 --> 33:03.211
I'll carry you if I have to.

33:03.712 --> 33:04.754
Ms. Song!

33:07.424 --> 33:08.758
How have you been?

33:13.763 --> 33:15.056
This is bad.

33:25.191 --> 33:27.359
I ended up liking you so much,

33:27.360 --> 33:30.613
even when
I couldn't explain myself to you.

33:36.953 --> 33:40.205
10. MY BIRTHDAY, THE DAY I DECIDED
TO EXPLAIN MYSELF DESPITE THE GAPS

33:41.583 --> 33:44.668
I feel like
telling you everything today, too.

33:44.669 --> 33:47.588
I think I should stop
hiding things about myself.

33:47.589 --> 33:48.714
Odd or even?

33:48.715 --> 33:51.051
- I wanted to tell you everything…
- Odd.

33:52.761 --> 33:55.304
But I knew my memories
weren't fully intact.

33:56.389 --> 33:58.266
I grew worried that acting rashly

33:59.809 --> 34:03.480
would ruin things between us
or hurt you in some way.

34:03.938 --> 34:05.190
And in spring…

34:05.774 --> 34:07.776
Will you not be here in spring?

34:08.526 --> 34:12.780
I'm going to use that trial
for the rest of my life.

34:12.781 --> 34:13.906
But…

34:13.907 --> 34:15.491
I felt frustrated

34:15.492 --> 34:18.787
that I couldn't talk about the future
with the person I loved.

34:19.704 --> 34:22.123
So I made a decision.

34:22.499 --> 34:26.627
I decided I'd slowly explain
what I could remember.

34:26.628 --> 34:29.422
Do you have time after the movie?

34:29.839 --> 34:31.633
There's something I have to tell you.

34:32.717 --> 34:34.928
I knew you would see

34:35.804 --> 34:37.180
how sincere I was.

34:42.394 --> 34:43.645
I wanted to show you

34:44.270 --> 34:45.980
that there's another way.

34:46.689 --> 34:48.982
I learned it through that person.

34:48.983 --> 34:52.069
She was just
someone who broadened my world.

34:52.070 --> 34:54.030
You felt like someone you miss

34:54.864 --> 34:56.782
called your name.

34:56.783 --> 35:00.286
You already did that for me.

35:05.125 --> 35:08.378
I thought it would be impossible,
so I scribbled it out…

35:13.842 --> 35:15.342
but it might be possible now.

35:18.012 --> 35:19.555
He went traveling with me.

35:19.556 --> 35:22.683
Hyeokchan was away during vacation
to help our professor.

35:22.684 --> 35:24.477
He asked me for a favor.

35:27.814 --> 35:29.398
I chose to never do anything

35:29.399 --> 35:32.735
that might get in the way
of her happiness.

35:32.736 --> 35:35.279
Thanks to you, I just realized

35:35.280 --> 35:39.075
that not digging up old wounds
is also a way

35:40.577 --> 35:42.954
of protecting their happiness.

35:45.081 --> 35:46.207
That was all about me.

35:55.258 --> 35:57.302
I should've heard him out.

35:58.094 --> 35:59.971
I should've listened to him just once.
:cue

36:17.405 --> 36:18.740
-  Is this okay?
-  Let me see.

36:19.240 --> 36:20.867
Good.

36:22.744 --> 36:24.453
Your discharge is complete.

36:24.454 --> 36:25.788
Congratulations.

36:25.789 --> 36:26.873
- Great.
- Let's go.

36:29.167 --> 36:31.001
-  Mr. Park is here.
- Ta-da.

36:31.002 --> 36:32.085
Here.

36:32.086 --> 36:34.963
- He's here.
- Congratulations on your discharge.

36:34.964 --> 36:36.382
They're beautiful.

36:36.841 --> 36:39.635
Let me give you a ride back.
I'll drop you off at SHIM.

36:39.636 --> 36:42.096
Manjae. Should we walk back?

36:43.056 --> 36:44.556
I want to take a walk.

36:44.557 --> 36:48.227
I want to breathe in the cold air
and the smell of winter.

36:48.228 --> 36:49.853
You'll catch a cold outside.

36:49.854 --> 36:51.021
Just take our car.

36:51.022 --> 36:53.148
They're right. You should get some rest.

36:53.149 --> 36:55.192
A winter walk?

36:55.193 --> 36:58.111
That sounds amazing.

37:10.375 --> 37:11.376
It's amazing.

37:12.669 --> 37:17.089
I thought walking and breathing

37:17.090 --> 37:19.175
were just natural things in life,

37:21.344 --> 37:22.345
but today,

37:23.429 --> 37:24.597
it all feels like a gift.

37:27.976 --> 37:29.310
I realized that too late.

37:31.271 --> 37:33.189
Seeing such a beautiful sunset

37:34.524 --> 37:35.900
and feeling the seasons…

37:37.151 --> 37:38.361
I could have always

37:39.320 --> 37:40.321
lived…

37:41.614 --> 37:43.824
like life was a gift if I wanted to.

37:43.825 --> 37:45.784
It's not late at all.

37:45.785 --> 37:46.786
From now on,

37:48.079 --> 37:50.832
we can do it all together,
little by little.

37:58.965 --> 38:00.299
In the meantime,

38:00.300 --> 38:03.886
we went through big and small changes.

38:03.887 --> 38:05.012
No need to hurry.

38:05.013 --> 38:06.222
- One at a time.
- Slowly…

38:07.056 --> 38:08.307
Good job.

38:08.308 --> 38:09.350
Almost there.

38:13.438 --> 38:14.480
Yougyum.

38:15.356 --> 38:16.690
What is it, Hadam?

38:20.445 --> 38:22.237
"Congratulations, you've been…"

38:24.449 --> 38:27.368
- Hadam!
- I'm a real med student now!

38:27.869 --> 38:29.578
Great job, Hadam.

38:29.579 --> 38:31.204
I can't believe it.

38:31.205 --> 38:33.624
Yougyum, what's going on?
Why are you jumping?

38:33.625 --> 38:36.668
Hadam's a med student now.

38:36.669 --> 38:39.004
She just got accepted.

38:42.383 --> 38:45.135
Hey. Why are you crying?

38:45.136 --> 38:46.553
You're not her boyfriend.

38:46.554 --> 38:48.305
I just got a call from the team.

38:48.306 --> 38:51.059
I thought it was over
after I went undrafted,

38:51.601 --> 38:53.645
but I got picked up by the Taesan Titans.

38:54.479 --> 38:56.146
I'm going pro!

38:56.147 --> 38:57.814
- Wow.
- Hey.

38:57.815 --> 38:59.066
Yang Changmo!

39:02.028 --> 39:03.029
Hang on.

39:03.655 --> 39:05.531
Hey, how am I jumping?

39:07.033 --> 39:08.825
Oh? It doesn't hurt.

39:08.826 --> 39:09.827
Really?

39:10.328 --> 39:11.578
It really doesn't hurt?

39:11.579 --> 39:12.830
No, not at all.

39:13.748 --> 39:17.084
It doesn't hurt!

39:17.085 --> 39:18.294
Sir! Mr. Cha!

39:18.878 --> 39:20.295
You shouldn't jump yet.

39:20.296 --> 39:21.881
Sorry.

39:24.634 --> 39:26.970
:cue

39:32.475 --> 39:33.476
Are you heading out?

39:34.394 --> 39:36.646
Yes, I'm heading out.

39:41.025 --> 39:44.653
He said he has feelings for me.

39:44.654 --> 39:47.948
He asked if he could like me,
and I said yes.

39:47.949 --> 39:50.242
But he's exactly the same as before…

39:50.243 --> 39:52.912
If you're free,
would you like to have some wine?

39:54.330 --> 39:56.999
Just the two of us.

39:57.000 --> 39:59.627
Just the two of us?

40:02.380 --> 40:03.839
All right.

40:03.840 --> 40:06.175
Sounds good.

40:17.353 --> 40:18.478
What is this?

40:18.479 --> 40:21.314
You just got surgery.
You need to regain your strength.

40:21.315 --> 40:25.027
It's a local specialty from Jeju,
made by a master artisan. They're tasty.

40:25.028 --> 40:26.987
- Mmm.
- Have them with your granddaughters.

40:26.988 --> 40:28.947
- They look delicious. Manjae.
- Yes?

40:28.948 --> 40:30.283
You should have some too.

40:34.328 --> 40:37.831
All right. They look delicious.

40:37.832 --> 40:39.374
Okay.

40:39.375 --> 40:40.752
-  Eat up.
-  Okay.

40:40.877 --> 40:42.419
Focus on recovering.

40:42.420 --> 40:44.546
- You should eat too.
- All right.

40:44.547 --> 40:45.964
-  Here.
-  Eat up, everyone.

40:45.965 --> 40:47.717
Thank you.

40:50.720 --> 40:51.803
Goodness.

40:51.804 --> 40:54.431
Mmm! They're so chewy.

40:54.432 --> 40:55.974
-  Good.
- They're so tasty.

40:55.975 --> 40:57.351
This is good.

40:58.227 --> 40:59.728
Mmm. It's delicious.

40:59.729 --> 41:01.855
"This was the email
from the Comets."

41:01.856 --> 41:04.691
"We watched the medical test video."

41:04.692 --> 41:06.651
"We would like to verify

41:06.652 --> 41:09.613
his rehabilitation progress
and other aspects besides the video,

41:09.614 --> 41:12.532
so we suggest conducting a final test

41:12.533 --> 41:16.370
at a local training center
as soon as possible."

41:17.246 --> 41:18.330
What?

41:18.331 --> 41:20.290
You have to go to the States for the test?

41:20.291 --> 41:23.086
They must be worried because of my injury.

41:24.295 --> 41:26.297
I'll go and try my best until the end.

41:26.798 --> 41:29.466
As you said, if I give up
without trying until the end,

41:29.467 --> 41:31.593
all that will be left is regret.

41:31.594 --> 41:32.595
All right.

41:33.054 --> 41:36.139
Go and show them everything you've got,

41:36.140 --> 41:37.266
and leave no regrets.

41:41.062 --> 41:42.105
Let's do this!

41:42.605 --> 41:43.606
Let's do this!

41:44.232 --> 41:45.233
Gather our strength.

41:45.858 --> 41:48.610
-  After many things happened…
- You can do it, right?

41:48.611 --> 41:49.821
…during fall and winter,

41:50.488 --> 41:52.990
the seasons passed…

41:56.369 --> 41:57.912
It really is spring.

41:58.746 --> 42:00.413
And winter began to meet...

42:00.414 --> 42:02.750
...the beginning of spring.

42:05.086 --> 42:09.965
However, the man who offered
a fun spring picnic

42:09.966 --> 42:13.635
was nowhere to be found in spring.

42:13.636 --> 42:15.804
- I really wanted something cold.
- Wow.

42:15.805 --> 42:17.931
This is heaven.
It's so hot outside.

42:17.932 --> 42:19.015
Here.

42:19.016 --> 42:20.810
-  Thank you.
-  This is insane.

42:23.771 --> 42:25.815
Let's go see
the cherry blossoms in spring.

42:26.315 --> 42:27.525
We'll have…

42:29.152 --> 42:30.736
shaved ice in summer.

42:31.946 --> 42:33.280
Have some, Ms. Song.

42:33.281 --> 42:34.573
Come and have one.

42:34.574 --> 42:36.741
I'm okay. Enjoy.

42:36.742 --> 42:39.494
Even as another season passed,

42:39.495 --> 42:41.873
there was still no news from him.

42:43.040 --> 42:44.458
:cue

42:55.845 --> 43:00.391
GERANIUM
I CAN'T STOP THINKING OF YOU

43:24.332 --> 43:25.540
It's that cloud, right?

43:25.541 --> 43:27.751
The one that Ms. Song saw in Gyeongju

43:27.752 --> 43:30.712
that was the inspiration for Won's outfit.

43:30.713 --> 43:31.880
What was it called?

43:31.881 --> 43:33.925
- An iridescent cloud.
-  That's right.

43:35.343 --> 43:37.260
It's called an iridescent cloud.

43:37.261 --> 43:39.764
They say you have good luck
if you see an iridescent cloud.

43:41.224 --> 43:42.641
Come to think of it,

43:42.642 --> 43:45.685
it's already been a year
since we went to Gyeongju.

43:45.686 --> 43:46.811
I uploaded it.

43:46.812 --> 43:49.105
Everyone, like my post.

43:49.106 --> 43:52.652
Hey, Song Haran.
I'm not letting you slip away quietly.

43:54.070 --> 43:55.613
Give me a like on my feed.

44:12.588 --> 44:14.173
Here's a lucky charm.

44:14.840 --> 44:17.718
You know you'll get lucky
once you see an iridescent cloud.

44:21.681 --> 44:25.850
WE'RE USING THE DRAWING YOU GIFTED US
FOR OUR WEDDING INVITES!

44:28.521 --> 44:31.190
IRIDESCENT CLOUD ARTIST

44:36.445 --> 44:39.698
I JUST GOT A SURPRISE DRAWING GIFT
THANK YOU FOR THE GREAT MEMORY!

44:39.699 --> 44:42.325
"Gangneung, 16 minutes…"

44:42.326 --> 44:43.618
16 MINUTES AGO

44:43.619 --> 44:48.039
I… I'm taking the afternoon off.

44:48.040 --> 44:49.208
That's so sudden.

44:50.001 --> 44:51.002
What?

44:51.794 --> 44:52.961
She just got here, though.

45:05.641 --> 45:06.684
Hello.

45:07.268 --> 45:09.979
You looked so happy,
so I drew a picture of you.

45:10.479 --> 45:11.564
Can I gift it to you?

45:13.941 --> 45:15.608
- You're giving this to us?
-  Yes.

45:15.609 --> 45:16.610
Thank you.

45:18.779 --> 45:20.031
But what's this cloud?

45:20.740 --> 45:22.282
It's an iridescent cloud.

45:22.283 --> 45:24.200
They say it gives you good luck.

45:24.201 --> 45:26.244
I wanted to wish you fortune.

45:26.245 --> 45:27.705
Enjoy your trip.

45:28.456 --> 45:29.832
Thank you.

45:31.417 --> 45:33.252
You're here.

45:33.711 --> 45:34.754
It's so pretty.

45:55.733 --> 45:57.442
This is your sign, right?

45:57.443 --> 46:01.654
Have you seen anyone nearby
who draws pictures like this?

46:01.655 --> 46:02.781
I'm not sure.

46:02.782 --> 46:05.075
Have you seen anyone
who draws pictures like this?

46:05.076 --> 46:06.159
No.

46:06.160 --> 46:10.372
Hello, have you seen
an artist drawing pictures nearby?

46:10.373 --> 46:11.415
No.

46:13.209 --> 46:15.043
Excuse me,
can I ask you something?

46:15.044 --> 46:18.505
Have you seen an artist
who draws pictures with a cloud like this?

46:18.506 --> 46:19.964
We received one earlier.
:cue

46:19.965 --> 46:21.466
Isn't it this cloud?

46:21.467 --> 46:24.219
When did you see him?

46:24.220 --> 46:25.512
Just earlier today.

46:25.513 --> 46:27.264
- Four or five hours ago.
- Okay.

46:28.099 --> 46:30.226
Thank you.

46:58.087 --> 47:00.256
Where on earth did he go?

47:15.062 --> 47:16.313
Mmm.

47:21.527 --> 47:23.153
- Hello.
-  Hello.

47:23.154 --> 47:24.446
What a cool dog.

47:24.447 --> 47:26.073
- Can I pet it?
- Sure.

47:27.491 --> 47:29.033
Hi.

47:29.034 --> 47:31.286
I was close to a dog
that looked just like this one.

47:31.287 --> 47:32.288
Really?

47:33.414 --> 47:34.415
Bye.

47:35.291 --> 47:36.333
Bye.

48:00.858 --> 48:02.067
Sorry.

48:03.402 --> 48:05.279
I dropped my pen…

48:06.405 --> 48:07.490
again.

48:28.719 --> 48:29.720
I found you.

48:34.642 --> 48:36.268
I found you, Seonu Chan.

48:37.728 --> 48:38.811
Why?

48:38.812 --> 48:40.856
Why were you here alone?

48:45.236 --> 48:47.655
I'm sorry, I realized too late.

48:50.407 --> 48:52.618
Thank you for lying for me.

48:54.662 --> 48:57.373
Thank you for protecting my scars.

49:00.000 --> 49:02.293
No, it's all my fault.

49:02.294 --> 49:04.880
I wasn't the only one
who didn't know what happened.

49:05.589 --> 49:07.800
There are things you didn't know, either.

49:08.801 --> 49:09.885
It's all my fault.

49:10.636 --> 49:12.888
- I was being greedy--
-  No.

49:13.514 --> 49:15.349
You didn't cause that accident.

49:16.350 --> 49:18.060
Dr. Cha told me everything.

49:19.937 --> 49:22.897
Seonu Chan disappeared because of me.

49:22.898 --> 49:24.275
It was Hyeokchan

49:25.317 --> 49:26.694
who caused the explosion.

49:28.946 --> 49:30.739
And Seonu Chan was just a victim.

49:31.782 --> 49:32.992
I lied to him.

49:34.326 --> 49:37.580
I wanted to protect Hyeokchan
in any way I could.
:cue

49:41.750 --> 49:43.668
I'm sorry, it was me--

49:43.669 --> 49:45.296
It was caused by his lighter.

49:46.005 --> 49:48.464
It happened because Hyeokchan
turned his lighter on.

49:56.640 --> 49:58.558
Why would you
ruin everything like this?

49:58.559 --> 49:59.642
Stop it, Hyeokchan.

49:59.643 --> 50:00.769
Tell me!

50:01.395 --> 50:02.604
You have to remember.

50:02.605 --> 50:04.773
None of it was your fault.

50:05.608 --> 50:08.484
You've been talking to Haran
while I was away?

50:08.485 --> 50:10.028
Pretending to be me? Why?

50:10.029 --> 50:12.697
Did you think it was okay
since I asked you a few times?

50:12.698 --> 50:15.075
You were someone nobody even cared about.

50:16.410 --> 50:18.911
Did you get excited

50:18.912 --> 50:20.539
that someone paid attention to you?

50:21.040 --> 50:22.248
Kang Hyeokchan!

50:22.249 --> 50:24.084
You never hit Hyeokchan.

50:29.173 --> 50:30.883
It was…

50:40.267 --> 50:41.560
…Hyeokchan who hit you.

50:42.269 --> 50:43.937
Tell me!

50:44.396 --> 50:46.189
Kang Hyeokchan!

50:51.153 --> 50:53.197
I have something to tell you.

50:53.989 --> 50:55.032
Your messenger…

50:55.324 --> 50:56.325
What?

50:58.202 --> 50:59.745
While I was using your laptop,

51:00.245 --> 51:03.457
I kept chatting with your girlfriend.

51:07.836 --> 51:08.962
What?

51:11.173 --> 51:13.467
What are you talking about?
Say that again.

51:14.551 --> 51:16.011
We ended up

51:17.096 --> 51:18.389
chatting after that.

51:19.556 --> 51:22.226
But she thinks it was you.

51:24.269 --> 51:26.897
Hyeokchan,
you left your earphones in my car…

51:29.066 --> 51:30.067
Are you saying

51:30.693 --> 51:35.072
you've been talking to Haran
while I was away?

51:35.531 --> 51:36.532
Pretending to be me?

51:39.910 --> 51:40.953
Sorry.

51:45.332 --> 51:46.333
Hang on.

51:48.043 --> 51:49.128
Who are you to do that?

51:49.670 --> 51:53.090
Why would you ruin everything like this?

51:53.382 --> 51:56.884
I was already feeling guilty

51:56.885 --> 51:58.970
and wondering how to end things.

51:58.971 --> 52:00.973
My head was already about to explode.

52:02.307 --> 52:04.059
Do you have any idea what you've done?

52:07.980 --> 52:08.981
I'm sorry.

52:10.065 --> 52:11.108
Tell me.

52:12.943 --> 52:15.487
What sort of things have you been saying?

52:17.906 --> 52:19.616
Tell me!

52:23.245 --> 52:24.580
Kang Hyeokchan!

52:27.458 --> 52:30.585
Who are you to take away
my chance to end things peacefully?

52:30.586 --> 52:33.629
What am I supposed to do now?

52:33.630 --> 52:34.923
Why?

52:35.382 --> 52:38.009
Did you think it was okay
since I asked you a few times?

52:38.010 --> 52:40.304
You were someone nobody even cared about.

52:40.929 --> 52:42.723
Did you get excited

52:44.767 --> 52:46.268
that someone paid attention to you?

52:47.269 --> 52:48.812
Stop it, Hyeokchan.

52:49.521 --> 52:51.940
You're the one
who's been bad to your girlfriend.

52:52.566 --> 52:53.692
No, it's us.

52:54.109 --> 52:55.360
And you stopped liking her.

52:55.778 --> 52:57.446
So don't take it out on your roommate.

53:02.618 --> 53:04.243
You should leave for a moment.

53:14.588 --> 53:16.340
Are you crazy? We're in a lab.

53:16.799 --> 53:18.342
You're smoking too much these days.

53:19.051 --> 53:20.176
Watch yourself.

53:24.014 --> 53:25.224
Here for pickup.

53:29.269 --> 53:31.188
Never leave the waste container like this.

53:31.688 --> 53:34.190
Even a small leak will set off the sensor.

53:34.191 --> 53:35.566
Be careful.

53:35.567 --> 53:37.861
Sorry. I will.

53:39.112 --> 53:42.448
The waste container had
nothing to do with the accident either,

53:42.449 --> 53:43.992
because they collected it right away.

53:44.868 --> 53:46.369
I was a witness.

53:49.748 --> 53:50.874
It's not too late.

53:53.001 --> 53:55.796
Go back to Korea and meet your girlfriend.

53:56.839 --> 53:59.632
Explain everything to her
and apologize properly.

53:59.633 --> 54:01.425
And apologize to your roommate.

54:01.426 --> 54:02.718
You're the one

54:02.719 --> 54:04.971
who took his laptop
and asked him to cover for you.

54:04.972 --> 54:06.055
:cue

54:06.056 --> 54:07.391
You're in a dangerous state.

54:07.850 --> 54:10.810
Just go and get some rest.
I'll get going now.

54:24.032 --> 54:26.075
Chan, I saw a vapor trail earlier.

54:26.076 --> 54:28.661
But that made me want
to get on a plane to go see you.

54:48.932 --> 54:50.683
It wasn't your fault.

54:50.684 --> 54:53.644
The one who made me want to rush over

54:53.645 --> 54:55.105
and say "I love you"

54:55.522 --> 54:56.981
was you, back then and now.

55:09.286 --> 55:10.412
I love you.

55:10.912 --> 55:12.331
I love you, Seonu Chan.

56:16.978 --> 56:18.021
Oh, no.

56:21.650 --> 56:23.527
Where did he go?

56:24.111 --> 56:25.569
The detailed exam confirmed

56:25.570 --> 56:28.406
the shrapnel had shifted
and was stimulating his nerves.

56:28.407 --> 56:31.158
It caused memory disturbance
and hallucinations.

56:31.159 --> 56:33.536
Luckily, it shifted
to an operable position,

56:33.537 --> 56:35.497
so we were able to remove the shrapnel.

56:36.957 --> 56:38.125
Song Haran.

56:40.544 --> 56:42.503
But due to severe mental fatigue,

56:42.504 --> 56:44.965
he hasn't been able to wake up
for several days.

56:58.270 --> 57:01.148
We'll have to wait until he wakes up

57:02.149 --> 57:04.276
to see how the surgery
will affect his memories.

57:15.912 --> 57:17.079
Every time I see you,

57:17.080 --> 57:20.166
I swallow the same words
stuck in my throat.

57:20.167 --> 57:21.793
11. WHAT I WANT TO TELL YOU

57:25.338 --> 57:26.339
But…

57:26.757 --> 57:28.091
I won't swallow them anymore.

57:29.134 --> 57:31.762
I'm going to tell you
when I meet you today.

57:33.263 --> 57:35.055
The words I decided to say to you

57:35.056 --> 57:37.391
the moment my memories
were fully recovered.

57:40.187 --> 57:41.271
I love you.

57:46.443 --> 57:50.489
I LOVE YOU
I LOVE YOU, SONG HARAN

58:10.926 --> 58:12.886
I love you, Song Haran.

58:16.973 --> 58:18.642
:cue

59:29.129 --> 59:31.255
Music start!

59:50.066 --> 59:51.484
Congratulations!

59:59.159 --> 01:00:00.452
Congratulations!

01:00:23.433 --> 01:00:24.434
Okay.

01:00:46.206 --> 01:00:47.998
Kiss!

01:00:47.999 --> 01:00:51.085
- Kiss.
- Kiss.

01:00:51.086 --> 01:00:53.754
Kiss.

01:00:53.755 --> 01:00:55.006
Kiss…

01:01:03.848 --> 01:01:06.101
Oh, my gosh!
He really did it!

01:01:10.855 --> 01:01:12.816
Congratulations.

01:01:34.629 --> 01:01:35.921
Here.

01:01:35.922 --> 01:01:37.966
What? A baseball?

01:01:39.134 --> 01:01:42.052
The ball from my final strikeout
that got me my first win.

01:01:42.053 --> 01:01:43.596
I wanted to give it to you.

01:01:44.431 --> 01:01:46.891
I know I'm still in the minor leagues.

01:01:48.143 --> 01:01:49.144
Thank you, Hadam.

01:01:49.602 --> 01:01:51.270
For not letting me give up.

01:01:51.271 --> 01:01:54.733
Thank you for not giving up until the end.

01:01:58.028 --> 01:01:59.903
But now that I think about it,

01:01:59.904 --> 01:02:02.614
- we were so immature.
- What?

01:02:02.615 --> 01:02:04.950
We thought we'd feel too anxious
being apart,

01:02:04.951 --> 01:02:07.036
so we thought
marriage was our only option.

01:02:08.496 --> 01:02:13.125
But now, no matter how far apart we are,
I don't feel anxious at all.

01:02:13.126 --> 01:02:15.961
Right. I don't feel anxious at all.

01:02:17.672 --> 01:02:20.258
Have we… matured?

01:02:23.511 --> 01:02:25.722
Keep up with your rehab
during the offseason

01:02:26.181 --> 01:02:29.058
and get yourself in perfect shape
before the spring camp.

01:02:29.059 --> 01:02:30.143
Okay.

01:02:30.727 --> 01:02:31.728
And…

01:02:33.229 --> 01:02:34.563
sign this for me.

01:02:34.564 --> 01:02:36.357
I'm your number one fan, remember?

01:02:37.942 --> 01:02:38.943
I already signed it.

01:02:41.112 --> 01:02:43.907
TO MY NO. 1 DOCTOR HADAM
I'M ALWAYS ROOTING FOR YOU, CHA YOUGYUM

01:02:48.411 --> 01:02:50.121
I'm your number one fan too.

01:02:53.958 --> 01:02:55.209
Hey!

01:02:55.210 --> 01:02:56.211
:cue

01:03:00.799 --> 01:03:03.926
-  Isn't B better?
-  Yes, B is better.

01:03:03.927 --> 01:03:05.011
Who prefers option A?

01:03:06.137 --> 01:03:08.305
What? It's 3 to 3?

01:03:08.306 --> 01:03:09.681
What should we do, then?

01:03:15.063 --> 01:03:16.064
C.

01:03:17.023 --> 01:03:18.024
Ms. Kim!

01:03:19.484 --> 01:03:20.902
Ms. Kim is here.

01:03:22.112 --> 01:03:23.947
When you're not sure about both A and B,

01:03:24.364 --> 01:03:25.948
- then it's C.
-  But, Ms. Kim,

01:03:25.949 --> 01:03:29.243
you said you'd take a year off
with Mr. Park in France.

01:03:29.244 --> 01:03:32.579
A month was enough.
Taking a long break isn't my thing.

01:03:32.580 --> 01:03:36.625
All right, then I'll be expecting
an upgraded option.

01:03:36.626 --> 01:03:38.961
- Okay.
- Yes, Ms. Kim.

01:03:38.962 --> 01:03:40.629
All right, then.

01:03:40.630 --> 01:03:42.965
Let's prepare option C.

01:03:42.966 --> 01:03:44.049
Let's begin.

01:03:44.050 --> 01:03:45.384
-  Let's do this.
-  Clean this.

01:03:45.385 --> 01:03:46.469
Let's do this!

01:03:48.596 --> 01:03:50.515
Are you heading out now, Ms. Song?

01:03:51.182 --> 01:03:53.935
Congratulations on the bio-silk reorder.

01:03:54.686 --> 01:03:57.646
Right. Thank you so much.

01:03:57.647 --> 01:03:59.648
Is there something wrong?

01:03:59.649 --> 01:04:02.025
Even outside the office,

01:04:02.026 --> 01:04:04.069
you're always calling me Ms. Song.

01:04:04.070 --> 01:04:05.071
Nothing's changed…

01:04:06.906 --> 01:04:08.407
Forget it.

01:04:08.408 --> 01:04:11.869
Ms. Song Hayeong will head home now,

01:04:11.870 --> 01:04:13.454
COO Yeon Taeseok.

01:04:18.001 --> 01:04:19.209
Hayeong.

01:04:32.807 --> 01:04:35.143
Do you have to go home early today?

01:04:35.727 --> 01:04:39.063
If I don't, then…

01:04:40.315 --> 01:04:41.648
I mean,

01:04:41.649 --> 01:04:44.736
it would be nice to have dinner
and watch a movie.

01:04:46.779 --> 01:04:48.530
That sounds good.

01:04:48.531 --> 01:04:50.283
I like movies.

01:04:51.701 --> 01:04:52.827
Let's go.

01:04:55.538 --> 01:04:56.915
- This way.
-  Okay!

01:05:06.507 --> 01:05:10.177
Oh? What's that face?
You'd better not draw me weird.

01:05:10.178 --> 01:05:12.095
Come on. I'm Seonu Chan.

01:05:12.096 --> 01:05:13.514
Don't you know my skills?

01:05:14.182 --> 01:05:15.265
All done.

01:05:15.266 --> 01:05:16.893
Oh. Hang on. Give me just 10 seconds.

01:05:19.729 --> 01:05:22.565
Let's close our eyes
and exchange them on the count of three.

01:05:23.316 --> 01:05:25.568
One, two, three.

01:05:26.069 --> 01:05:27.946
Oh! You're pretty good.

01:05:28.404 --> 01:05:30.572
Why aren't you showing me yours?

01:05:30.573 --> 01:05:33.576
Ah. I forgot. Can you count again?

01:05:34.410 --> 01:05:35.702
All right.

01:05:35.703 --> 01:05:37.705
One, two, three.

01:05:58.101 --> 01:06:01.688
Let's go see cherry blossoms in spring,

01:06:02.272 --> 01:06:04.315
eat shaved ice in summer,

01:06:04.816 --> 01:06:06.233
see the autumn leaves in fall,

01:06:06.234 --> 01:06:09.653
and go snowboarding in winter.

01:06:09.654 --> 01:06:10.863
Will you share

01:06:11.572 --> 01:06:13.366
every season of life with me

01:06:15.326 --> 01:06:16.411
from now on?

01:06:27.380 --> 01:06:29.799
You should stand up to match the drawing.

01:06:30.466 --> 01:06:32.093
Huh?

01:06:33.845 --> 01:06:34.846
Hmm.

01:06:56.409 --> 01:06:59.202
Thank you for appearing in my life.
:cue

01:06:59.203 --> 01:07:00.455
I told you,

01:07:01.080 --> 01:07:02.707
I'll appear anywhere for you.

01:07:05.293 --> 01:07:06.960
Thank you

01:07:06.961 --> 01:07:08.421
for appearing

01:07:09.088 --> 01:07:11.716
in my life and in my winter.

01:07:46.334 --> 01:07:48.585
The cherry blossoms are beautiful.

01:07:50.254 --> 01:07:51.630
-  This looks delicious.
-  Here.

01:07:51.631 --> 01:07:53.424
-  Mm! Isn't it good?
- Mm!

01:08:09.607 --> 01:08:10.608
This is nice.

01:08:27.875 --> 01:08:29.000
Chan! Chan!

01:08:29.001 --> 01:08:30.961
I read somewhere

01:08:30.962 --> 01:08:33.630
that the seasons in life
don't come in order.

01:08:33.631 --> 01:08:36.426
What if winter suddenly comes to my life?

01:08:50.314 --> 01:08:52.150
It will pass one day.

01:08:52.692 --> 01:08:54.901
Even if winter feels endless,

01:08:54.902 --> 01:08:57.029
a spring breeze might blow someday

01:08:57.655 --> 01:08:59.991
once you keep fighting through it.

01:09:10.793 --> 01:09:12.794
I couldn't do that,

01:09:12.795 --> 01:09:15.047
so I probably won't be able to
send this message,

01:09:16.382 --> 01:09:18.592
but I hope that
when you're going through winter,

01:09:18.593 --> 01:09:22.013
a warm spring breeze blows by eventually

01:09:23.222 --> 01:09:26.350
and ends the painful season
before it gets too long.

01:09:27.059 --> 01:09:28.186
And…

01:09:29.312 --> 01:09:31.856
I hope that whatever season
you're going through,

01:09:33.316 --> 01:09:36.026
they're all radiant.

01:09:44.702 --> 01:09:46.662
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:10:29.664 --> 01:10:32.874
Thank you for watching.

01:10:32.875 --> 01:10:34.126
Be happy, everyone.

01:10:35.211 --> 01:10:36.963
Oh, no. It's over.

01:10:37.880 --> 01:10:40.131
What a radiant life it was.

01:10:40.132 --> 01:10:44.220
THANK YOU FOR WATCHING
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

